---
import { en } from '../../i18n/translations';
import { site } from '../../data/site';
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Base
  title={`Terms and Conditions — ${site.brand}`}
  description="The terms and conditions of Dorchain Studio for website improvement and maintenance."
  path="/en/terms-and-conditions"
  lang="en"
>
  <Nav t={en.nav} langHref="/algemene-voorwaarden" />
  <main id="main" class="legal">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Business</p>
      <h1>Terms and Conditions</h1>
      <p class="legal__lead">
        These terms apply to every agreement between {site.person}, trading as
        {site.brand} (sole proprietorship in formation), and a client. They are written for
        freelancers and business owners who hire me to improve, build or maintain a
        website. This is a courtesy translation; the Dutch version ("algemene
        voorwaarden") is the legally binding text and prevails in case of any discrepancy.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 1 — Definitions</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Dorchain Studio / contractor:</strong> the sole proprietorship of
        {site.person}, based in {site.city}, Chamber of Commerce (KvK) number {site.kvk},
        VAT identification number {site.btw}, reachable at
        <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Client:</strong> the individual or legal entity acting in the course of a
        profession or business (including freelancers) who enters or wishes to enter into
        an agreement with Dorchain Studio.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Services:</strong> all work Dorchain Studio carries out for the client,
        including designing, improving, building, optimising and maintaining websites in
        the areas of design, speed, findability (SEO), accessibility and responsiveness.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Agreement:</strong> any arrangement between Dorchain Studio and the client
        to provide services, including the accompanying quote.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Website scan:</strong> the free initial review of the client's existing
        website. It is non-binding advice, not an offer.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 2 — Applicability</h2>
      <p>
        These terms apply to all quotes, offers, work, agreements and services delivered by
        Dorchain Studio, unless agreed otherwise in writing before the agreement is formed.
        They also apply when Dorchain Studio engages third parties to carry out the work.
        Any purchasing or other terms of the client are explicitly rejected. If any
        provision turns out to be void or voidable, the remaining provisions stay in
        effect; the parties will then replace the void provision with one that serves the
        same purpose as closely as possible. These terms are written for agreements with
        business clients. Should an agreement nonetheless be concluded with a consumer,
        the mandatory provisions of consumer law apply in addition.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 3 — Quotes and formation of the agreement</h2>
      <p>
        The free website scan is non-binding and does not constitute a quote. Every quote
        from Dorchain Studio is non-binding and valid for 30 days from its date, unless
        stated otherwise. An agreement is formed once the client has accepted the quote in
        writing (including by email), or once Dorchain Studio has started work at the
        client's request. Obvious errors or mistakes in quotes or on the website do not
        bind Dorchain Studio.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 4 — Performance of the assignment</h2>
      <p>
        Dorchain Studio carries out the assignment to the best of its knowledge and
        ability, generally following the four steps described on this site: free scan,
        plan &amp; price, execution, and going live with an explanation. The client ensures
        that all necessary data, texts, images and login details are supplied on time;
        delays caused by failing to do so are at the client's expense. A stated delivery
        term is an estimate, not a strict deadline, unless expressly agreed otherwise in
        writing.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 5 — Changes and additional work</h2>
      <p>
        Changes requested by the client that involve extra time or cost compared to the
        quote are treated as additional work. Dorchain Studio informs the client in advance
        of the financial consequences where possible and only carries out additional work
        after approval, unless immediate execution cannot reasonably be postponed.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 6 — Prices</h2>
      <p>
        Stated prices are in euros and exclude VAT, unless stated otherwise. Costs charged
        by third parties (hosting, domain registration, plugins, licences, stock photos)
        are not included unless expressly stated in the quote. For ongoing services such as
        maintenance, the price may be adjusted annually; an increase is announced at least
        30 days in advance. For an increase of more than 10%, the client may terminate the
        ongoing service in writing within 14 days of the announcement, effective from the
        date the increase would have taken effect.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 7 — Payment</h2>
      <p>
        Unless agreed otherwise, Dorchain Studio invoices 50% of the quoted amount at the
        start of the assignment and the remainder upon delivery. Ongoing services are
        invoiced periodically in advance. Payment is due within 14 days of the invoice
        date, without any set-off or suspension. In case of late payment, the client is in
        default by operation of law and owes the statutory commercial interest rate,
        without any notice of default being required. Reasonable collection costs are at
        the client's expense, with a minimum in line with the Dutch Extrajudicial
        Collection Costs Act (WIK). Dorchain Studio may suspend work as long as the client
        has not met its payment obligations.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 8 — Ownership, licences and intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        All intellectual property rights to designs, texts, code, documentation and other
        materials belong to Dorchain Studio or its licensors, unless agreed otherwise in
        writing. After payment in full, the client receives a non-exclusive, transferable
        right to use the delivered website. Source code, design files and access to
        hosting, the domain and the CMS are handed over once the final invoice for the
        assignment has been paid in full; until then, Dorchain Studio holds a right of
        retention over these files and credentials. Unless agreed otherwise, Dorchain
        Studio may show the delivered website to third parties as a reference/portfolio
        piece.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 9 — Use of third parties</h2>
      <p>
        Dorchain Studio may use third parties to carry out the work, such as hosting
        providers, domain registrars, plugin suppliers or form services (such as
        Formspree). Dorchain Studio is not liable for failures, downtime or data breaches
        at these third parties, unless they result from intent or wilful recklessness in
        selecting that party.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 10 — Processing of personal data</h2>
      <p>
        Where Dorchain Studio, in carrying out maintenance services, has access to personal
        data processed by the client (for example via a contact form or CMS operated by the
        client), Dorchain Studio acts as a processor within the meaning of the General Data
        Protection Regulation (GDPR). At the client's request, the parties will enter into
        a separate data processing agreement for this purpose.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 11 — Warranty and correction of defects</h2>
      <p>
        If the delivered website fails to meet the arrangements set out in writing within
        14 days of delivery, Dorchain Studio will correct this free of charge within a
        reasonable period. This warranty does not cover defects caused by changes made
        after delivery by the client or a third party, by use that deviates from the
        agreed purpose, or by updates at third parties (hosting, browsers, plugins) beyond
        Dorchain Studio's control. Results such as a higher Google ranking, more visitors
        or a particular Lighthouse score are a best-effort commitment, not a guaranteed
        outcome.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 12 — Liability</h2>
      <p>
        Dorchain Studio is only liable for direct damage that is the direct result of an
        attributable failure to perform. Total liability per event (a series of related
        events counts as one event) is limited to the amount the client paid for the
        assignment in the 6 months preceding the event that caused the damage, with a
        maximum of €2,500. Dorchain Studio is never liable for indirect damage, including
        consequential damage, loss of profit, missed savings, reputational damage and
        damage due to business interruption. These limitations do not apply in case of
        intent or wilful recklessness on the part of Dorchain Studio. Any claim for damages
        lapses if it is not submitted in writing within 12 months of the client becoming
        aware of the damage.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 13 — Force majeure</h2>
      <p>
        Dorchain Studio is not required to fulfil an obligation if prevented from doing so
        by force majeure, including illness, outages at hosting providers or other third
        parties, internet outages and government measures. If the force majeure situation
        lasts longer than 30 days, either party may dissolve the agreement in writing, in
        whole or in part, without any obligation to pay damages.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 14 — Confidentiality</h2>
      <p>
        Both parties will keep confidential all information they receive from each other
        in connection with the agreement, unless there is a legal obligation to disclose
        it.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 15 — Ongoing services, cancellation and termination</h2>
      <p>
        Agreements for ongoing services (such as maintenance) are entered into for the
        term stated in the quote and, unless agreed otherwise, are automatically renewed
        thereafter for the same period. Either party may terminate such an agreement in
        writing with one month's notice, effective at the end of the then-current period.
        One-off assignments end by operation of law upon delivery and payment in full,
        unless an ongoing service has been agreed to follow on from it. If the client
        cancels a one-off assignment before completion, the client owes payment for the
        work already carried out, calculated pro rata to the agreed price, without
        prejudice to Dorchain Studio's right to reimbursement of costs already incurred.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 16 — Complaints</h2>
      <p>
        Complaints about the performance of the work should be reported as soon as
        possible, and no later than 14 days after the complaint arose, in writing and with
        reasons, via <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Article 17 — Governing law and disputes</h2>
      <p>
        Dutch law applies to all agreements between Dorchain Studio and the client.
        Disputes will preferably be resolved through mutual consultation. If the parties
        cannot reach agreement, the dispute will be submitted to the competent court in
        the district where Dorchain Studio is based, unless mandatory law provides
        otherwise.
      </p>

      <p class="legal__note">Last updated: July 2026.</p>
      <p><a class="btn btn--ghost" href="/en/">&larr; Back to the site</a></p>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer t={en.footer} nav={en.nav} />
</Base>

<style>
  .legal { padding-block: clamp(3rem, 2rem + 4vw, 5rem) var(--space-section); }
  .legal h1 { font-size: var(--text-h2); margin: 1rem 0; }
  .legal__lead { font-size: var(--text-lead); color: var(--ink-soft); max-width: 64ch; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .legal h2 { font-size: var(--text-h3); margin: 2rem 0 0.6rem; }
  .legal p { max-width: 68ch; color: var(--ink-soft); margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
  .legal a { color: var(--accent-deep); }
  .legal__note { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--muted); margin: 2.5rem 0; }
  .legal .btn { color: var(--ink); }
</style>
